article.description: Rodney Chatman scored 16 points off the bench and 11 players scored as Chattanooga routed small-school neighbor Hiwassee 102-54 in its home opener Wednesday night.
article.headline: Chattanooga wins home opener, beats Hiwassee 102-54
article.linkText: Chattanooga wins home opener, beats Hiwassee 102-54
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. -- Rodney Chatman scored 16 points off the bench and 11 players scored as Chattanooga routed small-school neighbor Hiwassee 102-54 in its home opener Wednesday night. The Mocs roared out of the gate on a 23-4 run to take complete control of the game against its National Christian College Athletic Association rival from Madisonville, Tennessee. Chattanooga built a 46-17 lead at intermission and outscored Hiwassee by 19 points over the final 20 minutes. Justin Tuoyo added 15 points for the Mocs, who shot 57.6 percent from the field, knocking down 38 of 66 shots from the floor, including 17 of 35 from three-point range. Daniel Graves led the Tigers with 14 points and Jay Cade added another 10. Hiwassee was 17 of 61 shooting from the field (27.9 percent) and 6 of 23 from distance. The Mocs beat Tennessee in its opener, 82-69, but lost to No. 6 North Carolina 97-57, both on the road.
